	 	<div id="heading">MENTAL HEALTH</div>
		<br><br>
	 	<h1>Facts</h1>
	 	<div class="cover1">
	 	   <div class="text1">
				 <div class="row">
					 <div id="cen">
						 <div class="col-lg-4" id="fl">
							 <b>AVERAGE SUICIDE RATE IN INDIA</b><br>
							 10.9 for every lakh people 
						 </div>
						 <div class="col-lg-4">
							 <b>PEOPLE SUFFERING FROM MENTAL ILLNESS</b><br>
							 60 to 70 million people
						 </div>
						 <div class="col-lg-4">
							 <b>SUICIDE CASES IN INDIA</b><br>
							 2.6 lakh cases per year
						 </div>
					 </div>
				</div>
				<br>
				 <p>Mental Health Illnesses is about a person’s mental and emotional well-being. Good mental health or being mentally sound would mean that one possesses a balanced mind, confidence, and self-esteem. A mental illness is a problem that significantly affects how a person thinks, perceives, and reacts.
				</p>
				<p>Mental health in India is still a fairly new topic and the mental health myths and taboos attached to this subject are prevalent to this date. According to the National Health program by the Ministry of health and family welfare, 1 in a 5 has some emotional and behavioral problems. 50% of mental health conditions begin by age 14 and 75% of mental health conditions develop by age 24. India is the world’s suicide capital having highest suicide rate in South-East Asia but still no proper prevention stratergy has been build up by now.
				</p>
				<p>In 2017, India acknowledged this by enacting the National Mental Healthcare Act “to provide for mental healthcare and services for persons with mental illness and to protect, promote and fulfill the rights of such persons during delivery of mental healthcare and services.”
  	 	</div>
